headline: Expedia Group (EXPE): Assessing Valuation After Strong Earnings, Upgraded Revenue Outlook, and New Dividend
summary: Expedia Group (EXPE) just posted third quarter earnings, showing both sales and net income climbing compared to last year. Alongside stronger performance, the company raised its full-year revenue outlook and confirmed a fresh quarterly dividend. See our latest analysis for Expedia Group. Expedia Group’s share price has rallied sharply, posting a 21.7% gain over the past week and a 44.3% return year-to-date as strong quarterly results, a raised revenue outlook, and consistent buybacks have...
